The paper deals with algorithms for maintaining the set of nodes reachable from a source node in a directed graph that is modified by edge deletions. This problem is related to data structures (cs.DS), graph algorithms (cs.DM), computational geometry (cs.CG), and algorithm design and analysis (cs.AL). The paper also mentions strongly connected components, which are a fundamental concept in graph theory and algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS and cs.DM, followed by cs.CG, cs.SI, and cs.AL.
